{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782890441974,"sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fLqHEYBJHiCrzJ8yjztbU9SA","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","offset":760,"limit":70},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n760: function buildLoopPrompt(loopType, specFolder, lineageDir, sessionId, lineage, researchTopic, options = {}) {\n761:   const skillFile =\n762:     loopType === 'review'\n763:       ? '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md'\n764:       : loopType === 'context'\n765:         ? '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/SKILL.md'\n766:         : '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md';\n767:   const agentName = loopType === 'review' ? 'deep-review' : loopType === 'context' ? 'deep-context' : 'deep-research';\n768:   const detachedIntro = lineage.kind === 'cli-opencode'\n769:     ? [\n770:         `This is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode lineage, not a self-invocation of the parent session.`,\n771:         `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n772:         ``,\n773:       ]\n774:     : lineage.kind === 'native'\n775:       ? [\n776:           `This is an explicit native fan-out adapter running through the command host's OpenCode CLI surface.`,\n777:           `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n778:           ``,\n779:         ]\n780:       : [];\n781:   const hasIterationCap = typeof lineage.iterations === 'number' && lineage.iterations > 0;\n782:   const stopPolicy = options.stopPolicy || 'convergence';\n783:   const stopClause = hasIterationCap && stopPolicy === 'max-iterations'\n784:     ? 'until config.maxIterations is reached; treat convergence before that as telemetry only and broaden review angles instead of synthesizing early'\n785:     : hasIterationCap\n786:       ? 'to legal convergence OR config.maxIterations, whichever comes first'\n787:       : 'to legal convergence';\n788:   const params = [\n789:     `  spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n790:     `  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: ${lineageDir}`,\n791:     `  session_id: ${sessionId}`,\n792:     `  executor: ${lineage.kind} model=${lineage.model || 'default'}`,\n793:     `  loop_type: ${loopType}`,\n794:     `  config.stopPolicy: ${stopPolicy}`,\n795:   ];\n796:   if (researchTopic) {\n797:     // A research lineage's phase_init binds research_topic from this line. Without it a\n798:     // fan-out research loop has no question to investigate and degrades to an empty topic.\n799:     // Review and context loops scope by spec_folder and intentionally pass no topic.\n800:     params.push(`  research_topic: ${researchTopic}`);\n801:   }\n802:   if (hasIterationCap) {\n803:     params.push(`  config.maxIterations: ${lineage.iterations}`);\n804:   }\n805:   if (options.convergenceThreshold !== null && options.convergenceThreshold !== undefined) {\n806:     params.push(`  config.convergenceThreshold: ${options.convergenceThreshold}`);\n807:   }\n808:   // Review/context lineages scope by spec_folder but the auto-workflow preflight\n809:   // still requires the same review setup bindings the native command path pre-binds.\n810:   // Without these, a detached CLI lineage can fail first-run initialization or infer a\n811:   // different setup contract than native lineages.\n812:   const setupBindings =\n813:     loopType === 'review' || loopType === 'context'\n814:       ? [\n815:           ``,\n816:           `Review setup bindings (emit before any writes, same as native PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS):`,\n817:           `review_target: ${specFolder}`,\n818:           `review_target_type: spec-folder`,\n819:           `review_dimensions: all`,\n820:           `spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n821:           `execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS`,\n822:           `lineage_mode: auto`,\n823:           ``,\n824:         ]\n825:       : [];\n826:   return [\n827:     `You are a ${agentName} agent running a fan-out lineage.`,\n828:     ...detachedIntro,\n829:     ``,\n\n(Showing lines 760-829 of 1515. Use offset=830 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"function buildLoopPrompt(loopType, specFolder, lineageDir, sessionId, lineage, researchTopic, options = {}) {\n  const skillFile =\n    loopType === 'review'\n      ? '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md'\n      : loopType === 'context'\n        ? '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/SKILL.md'\n        : '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md';\n  const agentName = loopType === 'review' ? 'deep-review' : loopType === 'context' ? 'deep-context' : 'deep-research';\n  const detachedIntro = lineage.kind === 'cli-opencode'\n    ? [\n        `This is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode lineage, not a self-invocation of the parent session.`,\n        `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n        ``,\n      ]\n    : lineage.kind === 'native'\n      ? [\n          `This is an explicit native fan-out adapter running through the command host's OpenCode CLI surface.`,\n          `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n          ``,\n        ]","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","text":"function buildLoopPrompt(loopType, specFolder, lineageDir, sessionId, lineage, researchTopic, options = {}) {\n  const skillFile =\n    loopType === 'review'\n      ? '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-review/SKILL.md'\n      : loopType === 'context'\n        ? '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-context/SKILL.md'\n        : '.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md';\n  const agentName = loopType === 'review' ? 'deep-review' : loopType === 'context' ? 'deep-context' : 'deep-research';\n  const detachedIntro = lineage.kind === 'cli-opencode'\n    ? [\n        `This is an explicit parallel-detached OpenCode lineage, not a self-invocation of the parent session.`,\n        `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n        ``,\n      ]\n    : lineage.kind === 'native'\n      ? [\n          `This is an explicit native fan-out adapter running through the command host's OpenCode CLI surface.`,\n          `Use the separate lineage directory and session id below as the detached state boundary.`,\n          ``,\n        ]\n      : [];\n  const hasIterationCap = typeof lineage.iterations === 'number' && lineage.iterations > 0;\n  const stopPolicy = options.stopPolicy || 'convergence';\n  const stopClause = hasIterationCap && stopPolicy === 'max-iterations'\n    ? 'until config.maxIterations is reached; treat convergence before that as telemetry only and broaden review angles instead of synthesizing early'\n    : hasIterationCap\n      ? 'to legal convergence OR config.maxIterations, whichever comes first'\n      : 'to legal convergence';\n  const params = [\n    `  spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n    `  config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: ${lineageDir}`,\n    `  session_id: ${sessionId}`,\n    `  executor: ${lineage.kind} model=${lineage.model || 'default'}`,\n    `  loop_type: ${loopType}`,\n    `  config.stopPolicy: ${stopPolicy}`,\n  ];\n  if (researchTopic) {\n    // A research lineage's phase_init binds research_topic from this line. Without it a\n    // fan-out research loop has no question to investigate and degrades to an empty topic.\n    // Review and context loops scope by spec_folder and intentionally pass no topic.\n    params.push(`  research_topic: ${researchTopic}`);\n  }\n  if (hasIterationCap) {\n    params.push(`  config.maxIterations: ${lineage.iterations}`);\n  }\n  if (options.convergenceThreshold !== null && options.convergenceThreshold !== undefined) {\n    params.push(`  config.convergenceThreshold: ${options.convergenceThreshold}`);\n  }\n  // Review/context lineages scope by spec_folder but the auto-workflow preflight\n  // still requires the same review setup bindings the native command path pre-binds.\n  // Without these, a detached CLI lineage can fail first-run initialization or infer a\n  // different setup contract than native lineages.\n  const setupBindings =\n    loopType === 'review' || loopType === 'context'\n      ? [\n          ``,\n          `Review setup bindings (emit before any writes, same as native PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS):`,\n          `review_target: ${specFolder}`,\n          `review_target_type: spec-folder`,\n          `review_dimensions: all`,\n          `spec_folder: ${specFolder}`,\n          `execution_mode: AUTONOMOUS`,\n          `lineage_mode: auto`,\n          ``,\n        ]\n      : [];\n  return [\n    `You are a ${agentName} agent running a fan-out lineage.`,\n    ...detachedIntro,\n    ``,","lineStart":760,"lineEnd":829,"totalLines":1515,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","time":{"start":1782890441960,"end":1782890441973}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_067fb8a0ec7a564e016a44bfc8178081918200b7f8672249ce"}},"id":"prt_f1c8d2739001905aBpeQhTWF68","sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","messageID":"msg_f1c8cc97a001zwU7Wdu3u9g9XY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782890442867,"sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_f3CkTBG4RLMlMRWrivIVamvi","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","offset":1020,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1020:     child.stderr?.resume();\n1021: \n1022:     child.on('error', (error) => {\n1023:       spawnError = error;\n1024:     });\n1025: \n1026:     child.on('close', (code, signal) => {\n1027:       if (settled) return;\n1028:       settled = true;\n1029:       activeLineageProcesses.delete(child);\n1030:       clearTimeout(timer);\n1031:       opts.abortSignal?.removeEventListener?.('abort', abortHandler);\n1032:       const effectiveSignal = timedOut ? 'SIGTERM' : signal;\n1033:       resolvePromise({\n1034:         status: timedOut ? null : code,\n1035:         signal: effectiveSignal,\n1036:         stdout,\n1037:         ...(spawnError ? { error: spawnError } : {}),\n1038:       });\n1039:     });\n1040: \n1041:     if (hasInput) {\n1042:       child.stdin?.on('error', () => {});\n1043:       child.stdin?.end(opts.input);\n1044:     }\n1045:   });\n1046: }\n1047: \n1048: /**\n1049:  * Build the subprocess command for a fan-out lineage.\n1050:  * Returns { command, args, input?, env } where input is stdin content when applicable.\n1051:  */\n1052: function buildLineageCommand(lineage, prompt, resolvedSandbox, resolvedPermission, options = {}) {\n1053:   const kind = lineage.kind;\n1054: \n1055:   if (kind === 'cli-claude-code') {\n1056:     const args = [\n1057:       '-p',\n1058:       prompt,\n1059:       '--model',\n1060:       lineage.model || 'claude-opus-4-8',\n1061:       '--permission-mode',\n1062:       resolvedPermission,\n1063:       '--output-format',\n1064:       'text',\n1065:     ];\n1066:     if (lineage.reasoningEffort) {\n1067:       args.push('--effort', lineage.reasoningEffort);\n1068:     }\n1069:     return { command: 'claude', args };\n1070:   }\n1071: \n1072:   if (kind === 'native') {\n1073:     // Native fan-out cannot call the LEAF @deep-review agent with a full-loop prompt.\n1074:     // For review runs this is the real deep/review command surface with a lineage\n1075:     // artifact override, so the command YAML owns init, loop, and synthesis.\n1076:     const args = [\n1077:       'run',\n1078:       '--format',\n1079:       'json',\n1080:       '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n1081:       '--dir',\n1082:       process.cwd(),\n1083:       '--command',\n1084:       `deep/${options.loopType || 'review'}`,\n1085:     ];\n1086:     args.push(buildNativeCommandInput(\n1087:       options.loopType || 'review',\n1088:       options.specFolder || '',\n1089:       options.lineageDir || '',\n1090:       lineage,\n1091:       options,\n1092:     ));\n1093:     return { command: 'opencode', args, input: '' };\n1094:   }\n1095: \n1096:   if (kind === 'cli-opencode') {\n1097:     // No --agent: current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it\n1098:     // on a top-level `run`. The default agent runs when none is named, and a\n1099:     // specific agent profile can be requested in the prompt body instead.\n1100:     const args = [\n1101:       'run',\n1102:       '--model',\n1103:       lineage.model || 'anthropic/claude-opus-4-8',\n1104:       '--format',\n1105:       'json',\n1106:       '--pure',\n1107:       '--dir',\n1108:       process.cwd(),\n1109:     ];\n\n(Showing lines 1020-1109 of 1515. Use offset=1110 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"    child.stderr?.resume();\n\n    child.on('error', (error) => {\n      spawnError = error;\n    });\n\n    child.on('close', (code, signal) => {\n      if (settled) return;\n      settled = true;\n      activeLineageProcesses.delete(child);\n      clearTimeout(timer);\n      opts.abortSignal?.removeEventListener?.('abort', abortHandler);\n      const effectiveSignal = timedOut ? 'SIGTERM' : signal;\n      resolvePromise({\n        status: timedOut ? null : code,\n        signal: effectiveSignal,\n        stdout,\n        ...(spawnError ? { error: spawnError } : {}),\n      });\n    });","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","text":"    child.stderr?.resume();\n\n    child.on('error', (error) => {\n      spawnError = error;\n    });\n\n    child.on('close', (code, signal) => {\n      if (settled) return;\n      settled = true;\n      activeLineageProcesses.delete(child);\n      clearTimeout(timer);\n      opts.abortSignal?.removeEventListener?.('abort', abortHandler);\n      const effectiveSignal = timedOut ? 'SIGTERM' : signal;\n      resolvePromise({\n        status: timedOut ? null : code,\n        signal: effectiveSignal,\n        stdout,\n        ...(spawnError ? { error: spawnError } : {}),\n      });\n    });\n\n    if (hasInput) {\n      child.stdin?.on('error', () => {});\n      child.stdin?.end(opts.input);\n    }\n  });\n}\n\n/**\n * Build the subprocess command for a fan-out lineage.\n * Returns { command, args, input?, env } where input is stdin content when applicable.\n */\nfunction buildLineageCommand(lineage, prompt, resolvedSandbox, resolvedPermission, options = {}) {\n  const kind = lineage.kind;\n\n  if (kind === 'cli-claude-code') {\n    const args = [\n      '-p',\n      prompt,\n      '--model',\n      lineage.model || 'claude-opus-4-8',\n      '--permission-mode',\n      resolvedPermission,\n      '--output-format',\n      'text',\n    ];\n    if (lineage.reasoningEffort) {\n      args.push('--effort', lineage.reasoningEffort);\n    }\n    return { command: 'claude', args };\n  }\n\n  if (kind === 'native') {\n    // Native fan-out cannot call the LEAF @deep-review agent with a full-loop prompt.\n    // For review runs this is the real deep/review command surface with a lineage\n    // artifact override, so the command YAML owns init, loop, and synthesis.\n    const args = [\n      'run',\n      '--format',\n      'json',\n      '--dangerously-skip-permissions',\n      '--dir',\n      process.cwd(),\n      '--command',\n      `deep/${options.loopType || 'review'}`,\n    ];\n    args.push(buildNativeCommandInput(\n      options.loopType || 'review',\n      options.specFolder || '',\n      options.lineageDir || '',\n      lineage,\n      options,\n    ));\n    return { command: 'opencode', args, input: '' };\n  }\n\n  if (kind === 'cli-opencode') {\n    // No --agent: current opencode treats `general` as a subagent and rejects it\n    // on a top-level `run`. The default agent runs when none is named, and a\n    // specific agent profile can be requested in the prompt body instead.\n    const args = [\n      'run',\n      '--model',\n      lineage.model || 'anthropic/claude-opus-4-8',\n      '--format',\n      'json',\n      '--pure',\n      '--dir',\n      process.cwd(),\n    ];","lineStart":1020,"lineEnd":1109,"totalLines":1515,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","time":{"start":1782890442854,"end":1782890442864}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_067fb8a0ec7a564e016a44bfc8179c8191976a4f97a869b830"}},"id":"prt_f1c8d2d3a001fPZX9YQtn6JAGf","sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","messageID":"msg_f1c8cc97a001zwU7Wdu3u9g9XY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782890443434,"sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_4BrxwIIPVaa5c4DlshJIcxXc","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","offset":1268,"limit":70},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1268:       stopped_signal: signal,\n1269:       stopped_at_iso: stoppedAtIso,\n1270:       status: 'partial',\n1271:       ...partial.summary,\n1272:       gauges,\n1273:       results: partial.results,\n1274:     });\n1275:   };\n1276: \n1277:   installFanoutSignalHandlers(writeStoppedSummary);\n1278: \n1279:   const { results, summary } = await runCappedPool({\n1280:     items: cliLineages,\n1281:     concurrency: fanoutConfig.concurrency,\n1282:     maxRetries: fanoutConfig.maxRetries,\n1283:     lagCeilingMs: fanoutConfig.lagCeilingMs,\n1284:     initialRetryCounts,\n1285:     onEvent: (event) => {\n1286:       const enrichedEvent = decorateSlotAccountingEvent(event, lineageSlotAccounting);\n1287:       updateLineageSnapshot(lineageSnapshots, enrichedEvent);\n1288:       if (enrichedEvent.gauges) latestGauges = enrichedEvent.gauges;\n1289:       appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, enrichedEvent);\n1290:     },\n1291:     worker: async (lineage, context) => {\n1292:       const hrStart = process.hrtime();\n1293:       const lineageDir = path.join(lineagesDir, lineage.label);\n1294:       const stateDir = path.join(lineageDir, '.executor-state');\n1295:       fs.mkdirSync(lineageDir, { recursive: true });\n1296:       fs.mkdirSync(stateDir, { recursive: true });\n1297: \n1298:       const sessionId = `fanout-${lineage.label}-${runId}`;\n1299:       const prompt = buildLoopPrompt(loopType, specFolder, lineageDir, sessionId, lineage, researchTopic, {\n1300:         convergenceThreshold,\n1301:         stopPolicy,\n1302:       });\n1303: \n1304:       // Sandbox resolution stays write-capable by default even for review lineages:\n1305:       // the review subprocess writes its own iteration artifacts (iterations/iteration-NNN.md,\n1306:       // deep-review-state.jsonl, review-report.md, resource-map.md) INTO lineageDir, so a\n1307:       // blanket read-only default would break those writes. The lineageDir-only write boundary\n1308:       // is enforced by the prompt ('Do not touch any path outside lineageDir') rather than by a\n1309:       // narrower sandbox; a path-scoped workspace-write would be the stronger fix if the CLIs\n1310:       // exposed one. Callers can still pass an explicit sandboxMode to override.\n1311:       const resolvedSandbox = resolveSandboxMode(lineage.sandboxMode);\n1312:       const resolvedPermission = resolveClaudePermissionMode(lineage.sandboxMode);\n1313: \n1314:       const effectiveSandbox = resolvedSandbox;\n1315:       const effectivePermission = resolvedPermission;\n1316: \n1317:       const { command, args: cmdArgs, input } = buildLineageCommand(\n1318:         lineage,\n1319:         prompt,\n1320:         effectiveSandbox,\n1321:         effectivePermission,\n1322:         {\n1323:           loopType,\n1324:           specFolder,\n1325:           lineageDir,\n1326:           convergenceThreshold,\n1327:           stopPolicy,\n1328:           researchTopic,\n1329:         },\n1330:       );\n1331: \n1332:       // Advertise a per-replica state dir hint to the child via SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR.\n1333:       // This is DETECTION-ONLY: the native CLIs read their own home env (OPENCODE_HOME /\n1334:       // OPENCODE_HOME / CLAUDE_CODE_HOME), not this var, so it does NOT relocate the\n1335:       // native lockfile. Real same-kind-replica isolation comes from each lineage's\n1336:       // unique artifact dir (lineage.label); remapping the CLI home to isolate the lock\n1337:       // is deliberately avoided here because relocating the home breaks credential/auth\n\n(Showing lines 1268-1337 of 1515. Use offset=1338 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"      stopped_signal: signal,\n      stopped_at_iso: stoppedAtIso,\n      status: 'partial',\n      ...partial.summary,\n      gauges,\n      results: partial.results,\n    });\n  };\n\n  installFanoutSignalHandlers(writeStoppedSummary);\n\n  const { results, summary } = await runCappedPool({\n    items: cliLineages,\n    concurrency: fanoutConfig.concurrency,\n    maxRetries: fanoutConfig.maxRetries,\n    lagCeilingMs: fanoutConfig.lagCeilingMs,\n    initialRetryCounts,\n    onEvent: (event) => {\n      const enrichedEvent = decorateSlotAccountingEvent(event, lineageSlotAccounting);\n      updateLineageSnapshot(lineageSnapshots, enrichedEvent);","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","text":"      stopped_signal: signal,\n      stopped_at_iso: stoppedAtIso,\n      status: 'partial',\n      ...partial.summary,\n      gauges,\n      results: partial.results,\n    });\n  };\n\n  installFanoutSignalHandlers(writeStoppedSummary);\n\n  const { results, summary } = await runCappedPool({\n    items: cliLineages,\n    concurrency: fanoutConfig.concurrency,\n    maxRetries: fanoutConfig.maxRetries,\n    lagCeilingMs: fanoutConfig.lagCeilingMs,\n    initialRetryCounts,\n    onEvent: (event) => {\n      const enrichedEvent = decorateSlotAccountingEvent(event, lineageSlotAccounting);\n      updateLineageSnapshot(lineageSnapshots, enrichedEvent);\n      if (enrichedEvent.gauges) latestGauges = enrichedEvent.gauges;\n      appendFanoutStatusLedger(ledgerPath, enrichedEvent);\n    },\n    worker: async (lineage, context) => {\n      const hrStart = process.hrtime();\n      const lineageDir = path.join(lineagesDir, lineage.label);\n      const stateDir = path.join(lineageDir, '.executor-state');\n      fs.mkdirSync(lineageDir, { recursive: true });\n      fs.mkdirSync(stateDir, { recursive: true });\n\n      const sessionId = `fanout-${lineage.label}-${runId}`;\n      const prompt = buildLoopPrompt(loopType, specFolder, lineageDir, sessionId, lineage, researchTopic, {\n        convergenceThreshold,\n        stopPolicy,\n      });\n\n      // Sandbox resolution stays write-capable by default even for review lineages:\n      // the review subprocess writes its own iteration artifacts (iterations/iteration-NNN.md,\n      // deep-review-state.jsonl, review-report.md, resource-map.md) INTO lineageDir, so a\n      // blanket read-only default would break those writes. The lineageDir-only write boundary\n      // is enforced by the prompt ('Do not touch any path outside lineageDir') rather than by a\n      // narrower sandbox; a path-scoped workspace-write would be the stronger fix if the CLIs\n      // exposed one. Callers can still pass an explicit sandboxMode to override.\n      const resolvedSandbox = resolveSandboxMode(lineage.sandboxMode);\n      const resolvedPermission = resolveClaudePermissionMode(lineage.sandboxMode);\n\n      const effectiveSandbox = resolvedSandbox;\n      const effectivePermission = resolvedPermission;\n\n      const { command, args: cmdArgs, input } = buildLineageCommand(\n        lineage,\n        prompt,\n        effectiveSandbox,\n        effectivePermission,\n        {\n          loopType,\n          specFolder,\n          lineageDir,\n          convergenceThreshold,\n          stopPolicy,\n          researchTopic,\n        },\n      );\n\n      // Advertise a per-replica state dir hint to the child via SPECKIT_<KIND>_STATE_DIR.\n      // This is DETECTION-ONLY: the native CLIs read their own home env (OPENCODE_HOME /\n      // OPENCODE_HOME / CLAUDE_CODE_HOME), not this var, so it does NOT relocate the\n      // native lockfile. Real same-kind-replica isolation comes from each lineage's\n      // unique artifact dir (lineage.label); remapping the CLI home to isolate the lock\n      // is deliberately avoided here because relocating the home breaks credential/auth","lineStart":1268,"lineEnd":1337,"totalLines":1515,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs","time":{"start":1782890443416,"end":1782890443431}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_067fb8a0ec7a564e016a44bfc817a8819184f62755a308d227"}},"id":"prt_f1c8d313b0016Jn6WCSNvf5y8I","sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","messageID":"msg_f1c8cc97a001zwU7Wdu3u9g9XY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782890443766,"sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_DxoV7PhKb42780jsIIxzIhvE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs","offset":150,"limit":70},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n150:   return number !== null && number >= 0 ? number : null;\n151: }\n152: \n153: function normalizeSalvageSummary(value) {\n154:   if (!value || typeof value !== 'object' || Array.isArray(value)) {\n155:     return null;\n156:   }\n157:   return {\n158:     salvaged: readNonNegativeInteger(value.salvaged) ?? 0,\n159:     failed: readNonNegativeInteger(value.failed) ?? 0,\n160:   };\n161: }\n162: \n163: /**\n164:  * Classify a lineage failure using only bounded process and salvage signals.\n165:  *\n166:  * @param {Error|Object} error - Error object from a failed lineage worker.\n167:  * @returns {{failure_class:string,retry_verdict:string,retryable:boolean,exit_code:number|null,timed_out:boolean,salvage:{salvaged:number,failed:number}|null}}\n168:  */\n169: function classifyLineageFailure(error) {\n170:   const timedOut = Boolean(error && typeof error === 'object' && error.timedOut === true);\n171:   const exitCode = error && typeof error === 'object' ? readFiniteInteger(error.exitCode) : null;\n172:   const salvage = error && typeof error === 'object' ? normalizeSalvageSummary(error.salvage) : null;\n173: \n174:   let failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.EXIT;\n175:   if (timedOut) {\n176:     failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.TIMEOUT;\n177:   } else if (salvage && salvage.failed > 0 && salvage.salvaged === 0) {\n178:     failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.SALVAGE_MISS;\n179:   } else if (salvage && salvage.failed > 0) {\n180:     // Mixed salvage: at least one iteration was recovered but some artifact/iteration\n181:     // markdown was unrecoverable or a top-level artifact went missing. This is a\n182:     // transient artifact-recovery gap, not a fatal exit, so it should be retried rather\n183:     // than consumed as terminal. Without this branch a { salvaged: >0, failed: >0 }\n184:     // lineage fell through to EXIT (fatal) and was never retried.\n185:     failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.ARTIFACT_MISS;\n186:   }\n187: \n188:   const retryable =\n189:     failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.TIMEOUT\n190:     || failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.SALVAGE_MISS\n191:     || failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.ARTIFACT_MISS;\n192:   return {\n193:     failure_class: failureClass,\n194:     retry_verdict: retryable ? LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.TRANSIENT : LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.FATAL,\n195:     retryable,\n196:     exit_code: exitCode,\n197:     timed_out: timedOut,\n198:     salvage,\n199:   };\n200: }\n201: \n202: /**\n203:  * Throw a synthetic fault when the DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT environment\n204:  * variable is set. Used by contract tests to verify that scripts\n205:  * handle injected DB and script-level errors correctly.\n206:  *\n207:  * @throws {Error} With code DB_ERROR or generic script error.\n208:  */\n209: function maybeThrowTestFault() {\n210:   if (process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT === 'db') {\n211:     const err = new Error('Injected DB fault for deep-loop script contract tests');\n212:     err.code = 'DB_ERROR';\n213:     throw err;\n214:   }\n215:   if (process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT === 'script') {\n216:     throw new Error('Injected script fault for deep-loop script contract tests');\n217:   }\n218: }\n219: \n\n(Showing lines 150-219 of 517. Use offset=220 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  return number !== null && number >= 0 ? number : null;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSalvageSummary(value) {\n  if (!value || typeof value !== 'object' || Array.isArray(value)) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return {\n    salvaged: readNonNegativeInteger(value.salvaged) ?? 0,\n    failed: readNonNegativeInteger(value.failed) ?? 0,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Classify a lineage failure using only bounded process and salvage signals.\n *\n * @param {Error|Object} error - Error object from a failed lineage worker.\n * @returns {{failure_class:string,retry_verdict:string,retryable:boolean,exit_code:number|null,timed_out:boolean,salvage:{salvaged:number,failed:number}|null}}\n */\nfunction classifyLineageFailure(error) {","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs","text":"  return number !== null && number >= 0 ? number : null;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSalvageSummary(value) {\n  if (!value || typeof value !== 'object' || Array.isArray(value)) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  return {\n    salvaged: readNonNegativeInteger(value.salvaged) ?? 0,\n    failed: readNonNegativeInteger(value.failed) ?? 0,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Classify a lineage failure using only bounded process and salvage signals.\n *\n * @param {Error|Object} error - Error object from a failed lineage worker.\n * @returns {{failure_class:string,retry_verdict:string,retryable:boolean,exit_code:number|null,timed_out:boolean,salvage:{salvaged:number,failed:number}|null}}\n */\nfunction classifyLineageFailure(error) {\n  const timedOut = Boolean(error && typeof error === 'object' && error.timedOut === true);\n  const exitCode = error && typeof error === 'object' ? readFiniteInteger(error.exitCode) : null;\n  const salvage = error && typeof error === 'object' ? normalizeSalvageSummary(error.salvage) : null;\n\n  let failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.EXIT;\n  if (timedOut) {\n    failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.TIMEOUT;\n  } else if (salvage && salvage.failed > 0 && salvage.salvaged === 0) {\n    failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.SALVAGE_MISS;\n  } else if (salvage && salvage.failed > 0) {\n    // Mixed salvage: at least one iteration was recovered but some artifact/iteration\n    // markdown was unrecoverable or a top-level artifact went missing. This is a\n    // transient artifact-recovery gap, not a fatal exit, so it should be retried rather\n    // than consumed as terminal. Without this branch a { salvaged: >0, failed: >0 }\n    // lineage fell through to EXIT (fatal) and was never retried.\n    failureClass = LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.ARTIFACT_MISS;\n  }\n\n  const retryable =\n    failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.TIMEOUT\n    || failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.SALVAGE_MISS\n    || failureClass === LINEAGE_FAILURE_CLASSES.ARTIFACT_MISS;\n  return {\n    failure_class: failureClass,\n    retry_verdict: retryable ? LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.TRANSIENT : LINEAGE_RETRY_VERDICTS.FATAL,\n    retryable,\n    exit_code: exitCode,\n    timed_out: timedOut,\n    salvage,\n  };\n}\n\n/**\n * Throw a synthetic fault when the DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT environment\n * variable is set. Used by contract tests to verify that scripts\n * handle injected DB and script-level errors correctly.\n *\n * @throws {Error} With code DB_ERROR or generic script error.\n */\nfunction maybeThrowTestFault() {\n  if (process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT === 'db') {\n    const err = new Error('Injected DB fault for deep-loop script contract tests');\n    err.code = 'DB_ERROR';\n    throw err;\n  }\n  if (process.env.DEEP_LOOP_TEST_FAULT === 'script') {\n    throw new Error('Injected script fault for deep-loop script contract tests');\n  }\n}\n","lineStart":150,"lineEnd":219,"totalLines":517,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/lib/cli-guards.cjs","time":{"start":1782890443760,"end":1782890443765}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_067fb8a0ec7a564e016a44bfc818048191bdf61c2663b8d3b2"}},"id":"prt_f1c8d32e3001lcLZXsCZwS6qYR","sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","messageID":"msg_f1c8cc97a001zwU7Wdu3u9g9XY"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782890444172,"sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_VId1cMf8zUVA3wdpk5sn49yE","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-salvage-recovery.md","offset":76,"limit":30},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-salvage-recovery.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n76: \n77: ---\n78: \n79: ## 5. ADVERSARIAL REGRESSION\n80: \n81: > Regression guard for a fixed deep-review finding. This scenario is adversarial: it PASSES only\n82: > while the bug stays fixed and is phrased to FAIL the moment the regression returns.\n83: \n84: ### Adversarial Contract\n85: \n86: - Bug under guard: a lineage that exited 0 but wrote no iteration artifact was reported as\n87:   fulfilled instead of a salvage-miss, masking a silent fan-out failure.\n88: - Must-stay-true invariant: an exit-0/no-artifact lineage must be treated as a salvage-miss\n89:   (salvaged or retried, then failed if still missing), never counted as fulfilled.\n90: - Pass/fail: PASS only if the command below exits 0 AND `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` still\n91:   contains the named assertions; FAIL if either is missing, renamed, skipped, or exits non-zero —\n92:   any of which means the false-fulfilled regression has returned.\n93: \n94: ### Adversarial Steps\n95: \n96: 1. Run `cd .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime && PATH=/opt/homebrew/bin:$PATH npm test -- tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` and require EXIT 0.\n97: 2. Confirm `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` asserts both `retries a salvage-miss lineage once and exits ok when the retry succeeds` AND `treats an exit-0/no-artifact lineage as salvage-miss and fails it after retry (not fulfilled)` — the latter uses an exit-0 stub (`writeNoArtifactStubBinary`) to exercise the exact bug-under-guard path, and `records exit 3 (all failed) when the only lineage exits non-zero`.\n98: 3. Record PASS only with captured EXIT 0 output; a prose-only, skipped, or absent test is FAIL.\n99: \n100: ### Regression Anchor\n101: \n102: | File | Role |\n103: |---|---|\n104: | `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | Fails if an exit-0/no-artifact lineage is counted as fulfilled instead of a salvage-miss. |\n105: \n\n(Showing lines 76-105 of 115. Use offset=106 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n---\n\n## 5. ADVERSARIAL REGRESSION\n\n> Regression guard for a fixed deep-review finding. This scenario is adversarial: it PASSES only\n> while the bug stays fixed and is phrased to FAIL the moment the regression returns.\n\n### Adversarial Contract\n\n- Bug under guard: a lineage that exited 0 but wrote no iteration artifact was reported as\n  fulfilled instead of a salvage-miss, masking a silent fan-out failure.\n- Must-stay-true invariant: an exit-0/no-artifact lineage must be treated as a salvage-miss\n  (salvaged or retried, then failed if still missing), never counted as fulfilled.\n- Pass/fail: PASS only if the command below exits 0 AND `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` still\n  contains the named assertions; FAIL if either is missing, renamed, skipped, or exits non-zero —\n  any of which means the false-fulfilled regression has returned.\n\n### Adversarial Steps\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-salvage-recovery.md","text":"\n---\n\n## 5. ADVERSARIAL REGRESSION\n\n> Regression guard for a fixed deep-review finding. This scenario is adversarial: it PASSES only\n> while the bug stays fixed and is phrased to FAIL the moment the regression returns.\n\n### Adversarial Contract\n\n- Bug under guard: a lineage that exited 0 but wrote no iteration artifact was reported as\n  fulfilled instead of a salvage-miss, masking a silent fan-out failure.\n- Must-stay-true invariant: an exit-0/no-artifact lineage must be treated as a salvage-miss\n  (salvaged or retried, then failed if still missing), never counted as fulfilled.\n- Pass/fail: PASS only if the command below exits 0 AND `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` still\n  contains the named assertions; FAIL if either is missing, renamed, skipped, or exits non-zero —\n  any of which means the false-fulfilled regression has returned.\n\n### Adversarial Steps\n\n1. Run `cd .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime && PATH=/opt/homebrew/bin:$PATH npm test -- tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` and require EXIT 0.\n2. Confirm `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` asserts both `retries a salvage-miss lineage once and exits ok when the retry succeeds` AND `treats an exit-0/no-artifact lineage as salvage-miss and fails it after retry (not fulfilled)` — the latter uses an exit-0 stub (`writeNoArtifactStubBinary`) to exercise the exact bug-under-guard path, and `records exit 3 (all failed) when the only lineage exits non-zero`.\n3. Record PASS only with captured EXIT 0 output; a prose-only, skipped, or absent test is FAIL.\n\n### Regression Anchor\n\n| File | Role |\n|---|---|\n| `tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts` | Fails if an exit-0/no-artifact lineage is counted as fulfilled instead of a salvage-miss. |\n","lineStart":76,"lineEnd":105,"totalLines":115,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-salvage-recovery.md","time":{"start":1782890444166,"end":1782890444171}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_067fb8a0ec7a564e016a44bfc818108191b28afda6e6f095f9"}},"id":"prt_f1c8d340d0013GUDByZt0AGJVA","sessionID":"ses_0e3774f05ffeAQ2wPKEyNPUx36","messageID":"msg_f1c8cc97a001zwU7Wdu3u9g9XY"}}
