8 If feasible, re-run the reducer against codex's real 50 iterations to backfill its findings; otherwise document as a follow-up in the implementation summary\n65: - [ ] T009 Run the full `deep-loop-runtime` Vitest suite; confirm no regressions\n66: <!-- /ANCHOR:phase-3 -->\n67: \n68: ---\n69: \n70: <!-- ANCHOR:completion -->\n71: ## Completion Criteria\n72: \n73: All 9 tasks complete; zero marker hits repo-wide; salvage naming test passes; root cause documented with evidence; full suite green.\n74: <!-- /ANCHOR:completion -->\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: <!-- ANCHOR:cross-refs -->\n79: ## Cross-References\n80: \n81: - Spec: `./spec.md` · Plan: `./plan.md` · Implementation summary: `./implementation-summary.md`\n82: - Source findings: `../../research/research_archive/20260701T071133Z-gen1/research.md` §4.2 (F-002/G-003), §4.2 (F-012/F-014), §3.3/§4.4 (F-019/G-009)\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:cross-refs -->\n\n(End of file - total 83 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"`[x]` complete, `[ ]` pending.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:notation -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phase-1 -->\n## Phase 1: Comment-hygiene cleanup\n\n- [ ] T001 Remove markers at `deep_review_auto.yaml:395,408,988` and `deep_research_auto.yaml:301,319,1099`\n- [ ] T002 Grep the whole repo for `F-[0-9]+-[A-Z0-9]+-[0-9]+` in comments to catch any missed instances beyond the 6 originally cited\n- [ ] T003 Add a lint rule (validate.sh or pre-commit) matching this pattern; confirm it fails against a test fixture containing a marker\n<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-1 -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:phase-2 -->\n## Phase 2: Salvage naming fix\n\n- [ ] T004 Write a RED test: salvage placeholder for iteration 1 should be `iteration-001.md`, currently is `iteration-1.md`\n- [ ] T005 Fix `fanout-salvage.cjs:112` to zero-pad the iteration number (match the padding width used elsewhere, likely 3 digits)","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/deep-loops